5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to parole; to amend Section 15-22-26, Code of
10 Alabama 1975, to further provide for parole consideration.
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
12 Section 1. Section 15-22-26, Code of Alabama 1975, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 "§15-22-26
15 (a) No prisoner inmate shall be released on parole
16 merely as a reward for good conduct or efficient performance
17 of duties assigned in prison, but only if the Board of Pardons
18 and Paroles is of the opinion that the prisoner inmate meets
19 criteria and guidelines established by the board to determine
20 a prisoner'san inmate's fitness for parole and to ensure
21 public safety. The guidelines shall serve as an aid in the
22 parole process and shall promote the use of prison space for
23 the most violent and greatest risk offenders, while
24 recognizing that the board's paramount duty is to protect
25 public safety. The guidelines shall be structured, actuarially
26 based, reviewed every three years by the board, after a
27 specified open comment period determined by the board, and
28 posted on the website of the board and include, but not be
Page 1

