29 limited to, the following:
30 (1) The prisoner's inmate's risk to reoffend, based
31 upon a validated risk and needs assessment, as defined in
32 Section 12-25-32.
33 (2) Progress by the prisoner and inmate in complying
34 with the Alabama Department of Corrections to Corrections'
35 plan for reentry.
36 (3) Input from the victim or victims, the family of the
37 victim or victims, prosecutors, and law enforcement entities.
38 (4) Participation in risk-reduction programs while
39 incarcerated.
40 (5) Institutional behavior of the prisoner inmate while
41 incarcerated.
42 (6) Severity of the underlying offense for which the
43 prisoner inmate was sentenced to incarceration.
44 (7) The inmate's employment while incarcerated.
45 (8) Any education the inmate gained while incarcerated.
46 (b)(1) The Board of Pardons and Paroles must give
47 consideration to:
48 a. The inmate's low risk to reoffend, as established
49 through the validated risk and needs assessment, as set forth
50 in subsection (a)(1);
51 b. The inmate's employment while incarcerated, as set
52 forth in subsection (a)(7); and
53 c. The education completed by the inmate while
54 incarcerated, as set forth in subsection (a)(8).
55 (2) The Board of Pardons and Paroles may give
56 consideration to any other factors contained in the
