57 guidelines.
58 (b)(c) Except as provided in Section 15-22-37, if the
59 board grants a prisoner an inmate parole, the prisoner inmate
60 shall be released from prison upon the terms and conditions
61 set by the board, and while released on parole, shall remain
62 in the legal custody of the warden of the prison from which he
63 or she is paroled until the expiration of the maximum term
64 specified in his or her sentence or until he or she is fully
65 pardoned.
66 (c)(d) The board shall clearly articulate its reasons
67 for approval or denial of parole for each prisoner inmate,
68 based on its established guidelines, and shall provide the
69 reasons for approval or denial to the prisoner inmate, the
70 victim or victims, the Department of Corrections, or any other
71 interested party upon written request submitted to the board.
72 The use of established guidelines for parole consideration
73 shall not create a right or expectation by a prisoner an
74 inmate to parole release. Additionally, the articulated
75 reasons for denial of parole release shall not create a right
76 or expectation for parole release. The guidelines shall serve
77 as an aid in the parole decisionmaking process, and the
78 decision concerning parole release shall be at the complete
79 discretion of the board."
80 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
81 1, 2026.
